he laser light\'s power to destroy hair follicles is rivalled only by the night-light\'s power to slay closet monsters. Harness the benefits of luminescence with today\'s Groupon to Body Essentials Spa and Wellness Centre. Choose from the following options:\n                    \n                      For $89, you get three laser hair-removal treatments for small areas (up to a $285 value). Click here for a list of available treatment areas.\n                      For $139, you get three laser hair-removal treatments for medium areas (up to a $450 value). Click here for a list of available treatment areas.\n                      For $189, you get three laser hair-removal treatments for large areas (up to a $900 value). Click here for a list of available treatment areas.\n                      At Body Essentials, trained aestheticians usher guests into an earth-toned sanctuary illuminated by sunlight streaming through picture windows. During hair-removal treatments, a Palomar StarLux 500 laser terminates unwanted hair quickly and safely using tough-yet-gentle photons that harmlessly pass through the skin and directly impact hair follicles for long-lasting hairlessness. Technicians can evict pesky hair from the bikini area and underarms, smooth landscapes of feet and hands, or exile errant threads from either side of the neck, full face, or forehead-beard. Lasers cause minimal discomfort for the patient due to being calibrated for empathy and small talk.','fromC$89','','2011-09-16',456,NULL),(539,'http://www.groupon.com/deals/moorpark-morning-rotary','http://assets1.grouponcdn.com/images/site_images/1580/0260/Moorpark-Morning-Rotary_grid_6.jpg?FYShX5jp','Moorpark Beer Tasting Festival – Moorpark','Beer tastes better when freshly brewed, just as cars perform better when their gasoline is freshly squeezed from a fossil. Tipple a tenderly crafted brew with today\'s Groupon: for $40, you get two tickets to the Moorpark Beer Tasting Festival at Moorpark Morning Rotary in Moorpark on Friday, September 30 from 5:30 p.m. to 10:30 p.m. (an $80 value).\n                      \n                        The Moorpark Morning Rotary\'s beer-tasting festival kicks off Moorpark Country Days with a celebration of Americana and an expansive exhibition of regional beers. During the festival, patrons roam amid a throng of vendors as music plays and amber fluids glint in through chilled glass. Wandering guzzlers can savor free samples of more than 50 types of beer from 14 local breweries such as Enegren Brewing Company, Ventura\'s Surf Brewery, Wolf Creek Brewery, and Restaurant and Stone Brewing Company. Ear buds spark at the guitar strums and vocalizations of String Theory, Holliday, Sound the Sky, Sonic Abatement and Steve Hur, five local bands that mount the stage for 45-minute performances. \n                      \n                        To fill drenched throats, festival-goers can purchase tickets for fare ($2 each) and sample the catered grub of Chronic Tacos, Garman’s Pub, and the association of neighborhood fruit thieves. Funds from the festival will contribute to the Moorpark Morning Rotary\'s efforts supporting local schools and community organizations.','$40','','2011-09-16',448,NULL),(540,'http://www.groupon.com/deals/nautical-nellies','http://assets1.grouponcdn.com/images/site_images/1603/1213/Nautical-Nellies-Restaurant_grid_6.jpg?13Eq5B7C','Nautical Nellies – Victoria','The monopoly tycoons of the 19th century traditionally did their wheeling and dealing at fine-dining establishments, cleverly concealing the fact that they still lived with their parents. Dine like a railroad baron with today\'s Groupon: for $20, you get a four-course prix-fixe lunch at Nautical Nellies (a $40 value). The four courses include:\n                      \n                        Root-vegetable velouté (a $6 value)\n                        Wilted spinach salad (an $8 value)\n                        Grilled chicken breast (an $18 value)\n                        Duo of mousse (an $8 value)\n                        Nautical Nellies\' chefs coax robust flavours from quality ingredients, catching the attention of taste buds as well as OpenTable, where it garnered a Diners\' Choice award. Palates awaken as velvety root-vegetable velouté collides with apple-ginger chutney (add smoked albacore tuna for $2), creating a matrix of taste and texture as delicate and dramatic as the power struggle between pepper and salt. Come the second course, diners hunt applewood-smoked bacon, walnuts, and sautéed mushrooms in a jungle of wilted spinach salad coated in layers of honey-dijon dressing. The main course plates a protein-packed grilled chicken breast beside chanterelle mushroom butter, grilled asparagus, cashews, and tarragon-scented rice pilaf that whispers romantic sonnets to the nose (upgrade to a 6-ounce peppercorn new york strip steak and fries for $10). During dessert, gustatory expeditions conclude when a duo of mousse unites Callebaut chocolate, wild raspberries, and lavender shortbread. Though not included with today\'s deal, servers happily suggest drink pairings from an extensive wine list to enhance each course or further enliven the atmosphere on the heated patio.','C$20','','2011-09-16',458,NULL),(541,'http://www.groupon.com/deals/deluxe-beach-restaurant','http://assets1.grouponcdn.com/images/site_images/1607/2081/Deluxe-Restaurant3_grid_6.jpg?J_wDCuLY','Deluxe Beach Restaurant – White Rock','One of Isaac Newton’s last theories was that taking in a good view while eating aids both in digestion and in the ability to squeeze milk out of coal. Prove him half right with today\'s Groupon to Deluxe Beach Restaurant in White Rock. Choose between the following options:\n                      \n                        For $50, you get a prix-fixe dinner for two (a $100 value) that includes:\n                        Two salads\n                        Two appetizers\n                        Two main courses\n                        Two desserts\n                        \n                        For $95, you get a prix fixe dinner for four (a $200 value) that includes:\n                        Four salads\n                        Four appetizers\n                        Four main courses\n                        Four desserts\n                        \n                        Deluxe Beach Restaurant\'s prix-fixe menu brims with international options bolstered by fresh, seasonal ingredients. Diners can inaugurate dinner with the roquette, whose candied walnuts add a flavourful complexity to savoury goat cheese, then welcome a troupe of tiger prawns balancing crispy pancetta on their balsamic-glazed heads. Grilled beef tenderloin with phyllo-wrapped mashed potatoes and an optional shiitake-port-peppercorn demi sauce argue compellingly for terrestrial proteins, but patrons may prefer to ransack fabled undersea orchards with the lobster, ricotta, and pear ravioli in champagne-shallot cream sauce. For dessert, delve into the dark chocolate mousse that sports a distinguished wig of whipped cream and strawberry coulis. While learning to play the spoons between courses, diners can take a break to admire the ocean view from the upstairs, or browse surface sand for lost doubloons from the main level\'s cocktail lounge and outdoor patio.','fromC$50','','2011-09-16',459,NULL),(542,'http://www.thedealmap.com/r/?id=309-D6E3BA29F41D7ACAEFF54AF816DBEDC1&x=CitiesPage','http://images.signpost.com/images/190/190/orig/71795/c6530e1cc952776e161f9b2baf624c8a.jpg','$35 For One Month Of Unlimited Group Dance Lessons ($120 Value)','806 East Camelback','$35 For One Month Of Unlimited Group Dance Lessons ($120 Value)','','2011-09-16',620,0),(543,'http://www.thedealmap.com/r/?id=309-1AE46E3750329505448080983E6BD610&x=CitiesPage','http://images.signpost.com/images/190/190/orig/71798/161ceecfc335aaacf83f1e0509445f47.jpg','$49 For 1 Month Of Unlimited One Hour Classes At Koncrete Gym ($99 Value)','6949 E Shea Blvd Ste 