,'2011-09-27',5,NULL),(826,'https://1saleaday.com/family','https://s3.amazonaws.com/1saleaday/images/6161/original/solar-kit-3.jpg?1317070308','6-in-1 Solar-Powered Educational Robotic Kit With 6 Models!','“Hi. I’m here about the job?”\r\n \r\nGreat! Why don’t you tell me a little about yourself?\r\n \r\n“Well, I’m a 6-in-1 model, and I’m solar powered.”\r\n \r\n6-in1? Really?\r\n \r\n“Yup! I can do a boat, a car, a dog-like creature - ”\r\n \r\nThat’s enough, thank you.\r\n \r\n“Oh, okay. Sorry. So, um, do I have the job?”\r\n \r\nListen, Ace … I’ll tell you the truth. Even though I’m impressed with your multiple transformations, I’m a little concerned about this “solar powered’ feature. I mean, what happens if we’re indoors? Or underground? Or if it’s night?\r\n \r\n“I know solar power has its limitations, but there’s more to me than meets the eye. Really - ”\r\n \r\nWe don’t always get to choose where our missions are, y’know. We have to roll out wherever and whenever the big man says ‘go.’\r\n \r\n“I understand you would have preferred me to be powered by Energon, it’s just - ”\r\n \r\nUnfortunately, I don’t think there’s a place for you with the Autobots. Have you tried the Decepticons though? Optimus Prime would love it if some of our enemies were useless in the dark.\r\n \r\n                                                                 *        *        *\r\n \r\nLearn about solar energy while having fun. No batteries or tools are required to build the six different models in the Solar-Powered Educational Kit. Easy to build, the kit demonstrates the science of solar power.There\'s a solar powered puppy, 2 different planes, an airboat and more that can be created from the kit. The fun assembly is sure to get your child thinking about the various applications of solar energy and what else the sun\'s rays can power.','Price:\n$4.99','','2011-09-27',4,NULL),(827,'https://1saleaday.com/watch','https://s3.amazonaws.com/1saleaday/images/6157/original/73038SL.jpg?